caption: Delicious, finely crafted cocktails. Beautiful ambiance, and generous portions for their "small plates" qualify this place as a winner in my book. Great spot for a date or a nice dinner with friends. Staff was attentive and helpful. No reservations needed/taken for parties less than five people. All around a winning choice.
Life Goals: Clover Club at Clover Club. Beautiful classic cocktail bar with an amazing bar program. Can't miss the house drink but all other drinks we had were spot on, too.

Possibly THE best Brooklyn cocktail bar. Clover Club has an extensive menu of classic cocktails as well as modern craft cocktails that will never let you down. In addition to the great drinks the food menu will surprise and delight! I highly recommend the crisps with creme fraiche, brussels sprouts, steak on toast, and mac n cheese.
Very attentive staff, and good selection of cocktails
Been coming here for a decade and the place never disappoints. Amazing cocktails and delicious food.
Really good drinks and really great food , everything I ordered tasted great ! Wished they took card and or had a barcode to pay via phone like most modern places tho 😭
Awesome cocktails! Outdoor seating was fairly comfortable last night (40 degrees). Oysters and burger are great.

My favorite cocktail bar in New York City, and I’ve been to quite a few. If a gin sour style of drink is your thing, get the eponymous Clover Club cocktail and have a life changing experience. The drink prices are reasonable. The atmosphere is classy, warm and unpretentious. The service has always been gracious and efficient. The indulgent food pairs perfectly with the classic cocktail menu.
Nice warm cocktails for those cold days.Delicious foods and very clean.The best.
Nice place with delicious cocktails.Very clean place.
The review goes for the staff and their "mildly" rude/ passive-aggressive behavior. The place/ ambiance  and the rest was nice.
Has a nice warm cocktail menu for cold days to enjoy the outside dining. All of the food was delicious and the Burger is amazing, but make sure to add bacon
Best meal on Smith Street!
"Really enjoyed sharing a bunch of small high quality plates of food."
Love their duck hash!!!
Great drinks. Great food. Delightful outdoor dining.

Absolutely love their service, their cocktails are great. We’ve been there last week and they are following all the necessary procedures to make you feel fairly safe. If you have room in your tummy, try their bread pudding. I’m not a fan of bread puddings, but this one changed my mind!
Fun and adventurous cocktails
Such a pleasure having a world class cocktail bar right around the corner. The awesome food is a definite plus.
Iconic. A cocktail bar that should go in history books. Food is great too, but the drinks... just marvelous.

Ordering in can be hit or miss in pandemic times but Clover Club DELIVERED. This place was new to us, and what a find. Everything was amazing—the fried chicken ‘handwiches’ were standouts—the sesame bread was fantastic. Steak tartare was on point and the scallop crudo with watermelon was a refreshing detour. Many thanks Clover Club for an awesome meal from the comfort of our living room. Someday we’ll be able to patronize in person!
Best Old Fashioned in the city
This place has legit cocktails! The food is great too!  As for dessert highly recommend the strawberry short cake, probably the best I ever had!!
They're cocktails were really great! Interesting combos and tasted great
Great drinks..and food awesome..best taste in Brooklyn
Fun, welcoming atmosphere and good food and drinks. You can't go wrong here! This is an excellent dinner choice.
Food and drinks are amazing But smalls portions unfortunately
Great sidewalk space, great food, and service!
The food is good, but they’re so cheap with it. Bought some grilled chicken and they put like 4 pieces on it. Could of bought a whole chicken in the supermarket with that 😂😂
This place is SO GOOD! Go at least for their cocktails. Absolutely delicious. Their food is good too and I would definitely end the meal with their banana bread pudding.
I really want to like Rye a lot more because they make pretty fine cocktails here but it can just be unbearably packed and slow on weekend nights.

Absolutely love this place! The cocktails are delicious, the food is delicious, the service is always attentive. They have outdoor tables that are far enough apart to allow you to enjoy their establishment without feeling at risk.
Delicious food and great cocktails. The outdoor seating is nicely spaced and the service is attentive. I loved this place pre quarantine and am loving it now for outdoor dining and drinks.
Very good drinks and great fries and bread pudding
Love it! The drinks, the food and the ambiance were amazing!
Best cocktails in Brooklyn. Period.
fun spot.

Excellent for brunch, dinner, or just if you're looking for a few cocktails!  Priced very fairly. Definitely try their crisps with truffle aioli. The duck hashbrown and panna cotta for brunch are wonderful.  For dinner, try the lamb burger or hot chicken sandwich!
Nice vibe, awesome drinks and food. Friendly staff

I had the hot chicken sliders and mac and cheese with bacon which were solid. The most memorable aspects of the experience were the cocktails. I started safe with a rum-based old fashioned and then when happy-hour ended I moved on to a cocktail called Sage Advice made with "Oloroso sherry, pear, sage, gardenia spiced butter, fig bitters."  The sherry came through fully with each sip. I picked Sage Advice since it is rare that I encounter sherry-based cocktails. Maybe sherry is having a moment? It was a lovely experience from start to finish. The Clover Club's strength in making interesting cocktails with intriguing names really shined here.  I found the service to be really attentive from start to finish. I arrived without a reservation and was given a place to sit at bar and wait for a late arrival. As soon as my party arrived I walked over to the host who I over-heard saying they were booked on seating at the moment only to realize that they had taken notice of the arrival and lined up a table for us in a really seamless way. The waitress assigned to our table was also so attentive. We did not feel forgotten at all even as the restaurant got more busy.  I will definitely be coming again.
great cocktails.
It was absolutely fabulous!!! Food. Drinks. Service. Atmosphere. All on point.

I love this bar so much that I came while pregnant. Their "zero proof" drinks are delicious! Their general menu is full of interesting and yummy cocktails for any palate. Also, the happy hour menu should not be ignored! Those drinks are good and almost half the price of the other drinks on the menu.

The best cocktail menu and wonderful jazz on wednesdays — perfect combo. Very nice staff. Absolutely loved the place. And once again: the cocktails are very, VERY good. We will definitely come back again.
Fantastic drinks! And great service! Nicole was our server, and she had the best recommendations! We will be coming back!
Top-notch cocktails at a good price for the quality. Superbly balanced flavors in every drink I've had here.
Fun at night and during the day. Who knew brunch could be so tasty at the bar from last night?
Rude and impatient staff.
Excellent drinks and friendly service.
For a first stop from someone from out of town-it couldnt have been any better. There was a person for every aspect of your dining experience,  and they were swift and with a smile.
Great drinks.
Great cocktails, knowledgeable staff!
Totally awesome food and drinks. A must for Brooklyn.

Clover Club offers an expansive menu of cocktails. It's a great after-dinner place for some drinks and chats. If you are in the mood for food, the food is also quite delicious and serves as a more intimate affair with low lighting in the evenings.
Very friendly barenders. Fun mocktails. Get there early if you want a seat at the bar.
Five Five Five. SUCH as great staff. Sooooo nice. Food was amazing. Everyone was so chill...

Lovely brunch spot in the neighborhood AND they take cards (shame on other Cobble Hill businesses for only taking cash!)  The atmosphere of this place is very rich and lively and the decor isn’t that awful common Scandinavian minimalistic café look that millennials are magnetically attracted to.  Had the pork and grits, and the croissant French toast. All served very speedily and with a super friendly staff, I will be coming back for sure.
Love this place, breakfast is good , check it out
As usual - great cocktail, good service and nice vibe

Love coming here for Wednesday night jazz! Their cocktails are fabulous - the Blackberry Fool is my absolute favorite mixed drink ever. Even if it’s not on the current menu they’re typically able to make it upon request.
Great time great drinks great service
Great food, lovely staff. Can get busy during the brunch rush over the weekend. Would visit again.
This place has amazing craft cocktails, delicious food, and excellent service. I highly recommend it!

Third time there and still wasn't up to what I've read about it. I assume others are experiencing cognitive bias based on it's location or reputation, but giving it a hard look - it's really not worth what others have said. Some dishes seem just lazy to other times not coming together. The Mac and cheese is more cream than cheese. The pear on the cobbler was undercooked. The bean medley with grilled octopus just seems lazy. Broccolini was oil and not much else.  Pulled pork... is that from your US foods distributor? Couldn't tell the difference.  I'm kind of shocked by all the visits and coming up short. The cocktails are good, but there's more of a restaurant vibe here than a cocktail bar, and for a restaurant - it falls very short.
It was an amazing place. Happy 50th birthday to my Boss.
Wow soo good
Delicious brunch!

This place is one of my favorites. Amazing and extensive cocktail menu. Great, friendly, knowledgeable staff. The rare kinda place that works both as a neighborhood bar with regulars as well as a higher end destination bar. It’s a real cozy environment that feels both upscale and comfortable. The food is tasty and solid, though I wouldn’t come here to eat. Only downside is service can be a little slow, so keep in mind when planning your evening. Don’t miss the live jazz on Wednesday’s!

I was in Brooklyn, Madonna had cancelled her concert due to an injury and I needed to drown my sorrows so thought I might as well knock a World's 50 Best Bars bar off my list.  Didn't make up for Madonna, but they sling some great drinks so the night wasn't a total loss.
Great place forcocktails. My wife and I love coming here and trying out new stuff from their seasonal menu. Highly recommend!
Good food, cool cocktails, nice ambiance. Great for brunch or lunch.
Wonderful place for a cocktail, and the food is wonderful! Absolutely really good, would give it 6 stars if possible. Staff is really friendly as well.
Great place to come grab a drink or two with friends.
Amazing
Very atmospheric bar, great place to take a date or just chill with a small group of friends.
Awesome drinks, nice music and great service!
I love the ambience and the service.   The drinks were a bit pricey but the experience was fabulous!

Great and inventive cocktails.  The frozen drink with the matcha is the best.  Disadvantages are that it seems a little pricey for the area outside of happy hour prices, and service is fairly slow.  It took half an hour after ordering to get my second round of drinks.

Best overall restaurant in the neighborhood. Every item I’ve tried off their brunch, lunch and dinner menus has been fantastic which to me is the sign of a great restaurant. Their cocktails are also fantastic and the low proof buttercup’s cup is my personal favorite.  We’ve regulars here and in general, the service is good and the servers are knowledge. However, there are one or two hostesses who regularly work brunch who can get a bit of an attitude. Only calling it out because brunch, which usually has a 30-45 min wait, is worth the wait if you can get passed the first interaction you have with the hostess.

Excellent cocktails with service to match when you sit at the bar. The food is treated as an afterthought, though. The kitchen “forgot” to prep their spinach-artichoke dip and we waited an hour for it. The food was uninspired and many vegetable items included bacon, which was challenging for this vegetarian.  The next time I’m on Smith Street, I’ll happily stop in for a drink before I head to dinner somewhere nearby.
One of the best cocktail bars in NYC. Can't go wrong.
A long roster of classic concoctions as well as some modern twists accompany a small plates menu.
Seriously quality drinks. Awesome staff.

My favorite bar in Brooklyn!! The atmosphere is dark but welcoming. Cozy seats at tables and the bar. Great snacks but also an incredible Burger. Love the history and the classic cocktails!! Also a awesome back bar/room for your next party!!

The Clover Club became my go-to drink spot because of their extremely friendly service, and extensive cocktail menu that features unique house creations that are to die for.  Fun fact: one of the best cocktail bars in Philly has a couple of drinks that definitely look a bit ‘inspired’ by ones found at The Clover Club.
Really tasty drinks, and nice vibe. Will be back.

The place is just amazing..  I visited this place before  a couple of days with my office mates. The staff behaves friendly even if you feel confusion about order you can ask them about recommendation and they will help you to choose the best drink or food of your choice. They also have a great variety of cocktail i personally recommend you raspberry syrup because i tried this one.

Had gone with my friends yesterday for brunch and experienced the most tasty food and cocktails. Everything was full of taste and environment was also very good. Staff was also extremely friendly and efficient. Had spend great time with friends there with extremely tasty brunch.
Great cocktails and service.

Went for brunch on Saturday, and we had a great meal. Cocktails were unsurprisingly on-point (living up to their James Beard nod). Brunch dishes were also quite good - chorizo, manchego egg bake was amazing, and the bacon sampler and deviled eggs were also tasty. Although the menu items are heavy, portion sizes are reasonable.
Amazing drinks
Amazed by the sheer quality. Daring yet excellent combination of flavours, both the cocktails and the dishes.
Good food and good service. Excellent atmosphere
Had some incredibly nice cocktails and the live music was just fantastic! A very cozy bar with comfortable seating.

Went to Clover Club with work colleagues on a Monday evening - - fantastic place!  Gwen (hostess) and Danielle (server) were lots of fun, had great conversations with both.  Our group of 4 shared a few small and large plates, all the food and cocktails were excellent.  If you're undecided about your order, definitely ask your server for recommendations - Danielle was spot-on with her recs.  Will definitely be back next time we're in Brooklyn!

Love this place! Food and people were inviting.  Warm atmosphere and quiet enough to have a one on convo if going late night. Fun for friends night out or date night! Desserts so good that I'd find excuse to come alone too!
Excellent cocktails, tough to go wrong any of the options; The green giant is a refreshing summer choice.
Classy, relaxing atmosophere for drinks and conversation. Great place to press pause amidst the insanity of city life, Always felt welcome here.
Excellent Martini, delicious small plates of lamb chops, octopus, and grilled brussels sprouts.

The Beet and Dill cured salmon was one of the best things I ever had. My drink was quite good as well. It was a Maui Mule I believe.  The deviled eggs that I came here for were a bit tasteless though, and any flavor that was there wasn't very good. Overall though, the main course was so good it was hard to be disappointed.
Great place for a party. The bartender was great!

Love this place. I even got engaged here. The staff is always nice and friendly. They have the best fried chicken you'll ever have. I also recommend the crisps. Their drinks are fantastic. I recommend the Throne of Blood, or anything with scotch. The best spot is by the fireplace in the back!

Everything was very tasty. But the portions are minute, the drinks aren't very strong, and the prices are very steep. Presentations of food also left something to be desired. Deviled eggs $9. Smallest portion I've ever seen. Was comical. Lacked salt. $17 for half a piece of fish on some veg. The hanger steak was very decent and a fine portion. But at the end of the day it's a Jamee steak cut -- and very poorly cut before plated. Totally destroyed. Lovely sauce. Burger was delicious but played in the most absurd manner. Delicious cocktails but $14 and they are weak as hell. Probably what you'd except from the neighborhood. Moderately boring folk who can't quite distinguish between food worth paying for and food which is overpriced. Tasty though. And probably worth a date for a drink at the bar.

Easily one of the best bars in the city.  The cocktails are incredible.  The bar always has a lowkey vibe which is great for a nightcap.  I went here for a party a few years ago and they have a beautiful backroom.

Unbelievable. From drinks to dessert, the food here is insane. Insanely good. I got a shot of chocolate liqueur made in site that hit the spot perfectly, we ordered chips and dip that was perfect, pork sliders I didn't taste but it looked amazing; it also came with chips; I got steak and frites that came with a delicious side of greens and dressing. The risotto was perfection. The octopus seriously stole the show. Literal foodgasm. I liked the waffle more than the duck confit. We also got steak on toast, and fried chicken. I did not love the pear punch, but luckily the waitress continuously kept refilling our water glasses without needing to be asked. Extra points for that! Dessert is where I swooned. I got bread pudding that literally had me moaning and my friend got Panna Cotta which was made to perfection. I dream of when I can come back again.

The clover club ia a beautiful space. If you are visiting NYC make time to check it out. If you are a resident, get there as soon as possible! The atmosphere is great and the bartenders are friendly. The clover club is certainly a place I would recommend.

The best baked eggs I have ever had, very flavourful and cheesy. Only thing is they don't serve any espresso coffee...just drip coffee or ice coffee. But their cocktail is good as my friends said.

Great happy hour

One of my biggest pet peeves about bars and restaurants is that many don't cross over well. You may have a fantastic cocktail at a bar, but they serve no food, or passable bar food or have an amazing meal, but all that's on tap is basic mixed drinks. Much like getting a partner who can "do both" (whatever that means), the Clover Club bridges the gap between delicious bites and amazing drinks.  After seeing a movie nearby and wanting a to drink and eat, we came upon the Clover Club. Sitting in a quieter back room, we ordered a round of the Improved Whiskey Cocktails and some burgers. Although the cocktails took a few minutes to be brought to the table, once we got them it was well worth the wait. The key to improving a Whiskey Cocktail? Adding more whisky! I also got a Prime Beef Burger, a juicy delicious piece of meat, which paired very nicely with the whiskey.  After we all finished and paid the bill, the waitress dropped by again and gave us all whiskey sours on the house - maybe because they were free, but they tasted even better than the Improved Whiskey Cocktail.  Overall a great, if not a bit expensive, lounge and bar and a great part of the neighborhood

This place is nice to sit with some drinks and chat. I came here with a group and we sat for a while. Prices are reasonable and the wines are good. They dim the lights as the evening progresses so the ambience gets cozier and date- like. Sadly they don't have a happy hour on weekends.  I tried the chips fried in duck fat which were really good and the cornflake covered shrimp. Would recommend both. We also got the olives which were good, relatively fresh.  They do have a fireplace section in the back which they let out for events. But that's probably the best place to be especially in the winter.
